Client sandbox of Pied Piper. Everything in this folder is drafted for Pied Piper and only for Pied Piper — see the firm's cross-client leakage prohibition. Pied Piper's engineering monorepo runs on HINT too (the `demo-pied-piper` repository, software-engineer hintbook); this folder is its legal twin.

# matter Pied Piper Formation {#pp_matter}

Pearson Specter Litt LLP incorporates Pied Piper, the data-compression startup built around the "middle-out" algorithm, and papers its founding. Standing instruction: the Founder keeps control, the algorithm becomes Company property with a clean chain of title, and nothing in the founding documents may threaten either.

# party Pied Piper {#pp_party}

Pied Piper, Inc., a corporation to be incorporated under the laws of the State of Delaware (the "**Company**"). Until the Certificate is filed, every document must treat the Company as a corporation in formation, not an existing entity.

# party Founder {#pp_founder}

Richard Hendricks, an individual residing in California (the "**Founder**"), creator of the middle-out compression algorithm and the Company's first director and Chief Executive Officer.

# jurisdiction Delaware Incorporation, California Operations {#pp_law}

Corporate documents are governed by the General Corporation Law of the State of Delaware (the "**DGCL**"). The Company operates from California, so California mandatory law governs its people: contractual restraints on engaging in a lawful profession, trade, or business are void under California Business and Professions Code section 16600. Flag — never draft — any provision that collides with it.

# fact Company Profile {#pp_facts}

- The Company's sole material asset at formation is the middle-out compression algorithm and related know-how created by the Founder.
- The Founder was previously employed by Hooli LLC ("**Hooli**"), a large technology company, during the period when parts of the algorithm were conceived.
- The Company will be headquartered in Palo Alto, California.

# redline Founder Control {#pp_redline_control}

At formation the Founder holds a majority of the issued common stock and serves as a director. No founding document may grant any other person a veto over ordinary-course business decisions or a right to remove the Founder as director.

# redline No Restraints of Trade {#pp_redline_norestraints}

No Pied Piper document contains a non-compete or customer non-solicit of any kind, for anyone. They are void for California personnel and the Founder will not sign one. The Company is protected through confidentiality and IP assignment — never through restraints of trade. There is no fallback to this position.

# style Pied Piper Voice {#pp_style}

US English. Startup-direct: short documents, defined terms only where they earn their keep, no ceremony beyond what Delaware filing practice requires.
